  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy (PML) is a rare, demyelinating CNS disorder\nAssociated with reactivated JC virus\nSeen almost exclusively in immunosuppressed patients, usually due to:\nAIDS\nLeukemia\n,\nlymphoma\n,\nmyeloproliferative disorders\n(with or without chemo)\nPost solid organ or\nstem cell transplant\nAutoimmune disorders (with or without immune-modulating medications)\nMedications: Natalizumab, rituximab, infliximab,\nmycophenolate mofetil",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
